The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, January 20, 2004 				 Essar clears hurdle to refinery 
 OUR LEGAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Jan. 19: The Supreme Court today allowed the Essar group to go ahead with its proposed oil refinery at Jamnagar, Gujarat with an estimated cost of Rs 10,000 crore.																								The refinery has been in the embryonic stage for over a decade now as multiple litigations were preventing its completion because of environmental violations. 																								Its pipelines pass through a marine national park and a natural sanctuary at Vadinar in Gujarat. 																								A division bench of Justices Ruma Pal and B. . Srikrishna, in todays proceedings allowed an appeal of Essar Oil and observed that the company was entitled to proceed with the project. 
